The paper deals with the problem of signal recovery from corrupted sub-Gaussian measurements, which is a common problem in information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), signal processing (cs.SP), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and statistics (cs.SI). The paper's focus on matrix deviation inequalities and structured signal recovery suggests that it is more likely to belong to cs.IT and cs.LG, followed by cs.SP, cs.NA, and cs.SI.
